x4freetext: A 94-mug/cm**2 Sm-144 target, enriched to 88.6% and
supported on a 30-mug/cm**2 carbon backing, was used.

x4codes.hlp: Comision Nacional de Energia Atomica, Buenos Aires, Argentina

x4freetext: A five 150-mum surface barrier silicon counters
with energy resolution approx 700-800-KeV. A monitor
detector was placed at 20-degree for normalization.
the elastic and inelastic peaks were not resolved.
Therefore, in this angular range the differential cross
sections for the elastic scattering include a small
contribution less than 5% due to the inelastic channel.
The main contributions to uncertainties in the
evaluation of the cross sections arise from-
the unfolding procedure of the elastic and inelastic
peaks, background subtraction and statistical errors
(the error bars of the figures take into account all
Systematic errors arising from uncertainties in the
position of the monitor, in the evaluation of solid
angles and in the contribution of target contaminants
